grSerNum.name: grSerNum
grSerNum.description: The serial number of this unit.

grSystemName.name: grSystemName
grSystemName.description: The name given to this router.

grSystemPasswd.name: grSystemPasswd
grSystemPasswd.description: The console password for direct or telnet console access.

grdBaseRev.name: grdBaseRev
grdBaseRev.description: Indicates revision of the configuration database.

grSoftwareRev.name: grSoftwareRev
grSoftwareRev.description: This attribute provides the application (router) software revision number.

grFirmwareRev.name: grFirmwareRev
grFirmwareRev.description: This attribute provides the boot S/W revision number.

grReset.name: grReset
grReset.description: Resets the box. A read on this object will return a zero value.

grDateAndTime.name: grDateAndTime
grDateAndTime.description: This object displays the current date and time in the format as specified in RFC 1443 for the DateAndTime textual convention.

grSwitchPosition.name: grSwitchPosition
grSwitchPosition.description: This object indicates the position of the Console/WAN switch position.

grPhysNameTable.name: grPhysNameTable
grPhysNameTable.description: A table containing assigned Ascii names to the physical ports

grPhysNameEntry.name: grPhysNameEntry
grPhysNameEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains a name that has been assigned by the router to this physical interface.

grPhysPortName.name: grPhysPortName
grPhysPortName.description: This object indicates the Ascii name assigned by the router to this physical port.

grPhysPortTable.name: grPhysPortTable
grPhysPortTable.description: A table containing information about physical WAN configuration information.

grPhysPortEntry.name: grPhysPortEntry
grPhysPortEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains information about a specific physical WAN interface.

grPhysPortWanType.name: grPhysPortWanType
grPhysPortWanType.description: Determines the call setup/teardown signalling to the attached device.

grPhysPortSignalling.name: grPhysPortSignalling
grPhysPortSignalling.description: This object indicates the type of physical interface signalling used to attached device.

grPhysPortSpeed.name: grPhysPortSpeed
grPhysPortSpeed.description: This object indicates the speed of the physical interface.

grPhysPortCallType.name: grPhysPortCallType
grPhysPortCallType.description: This object indicates whether or not it will originate calls only, accept calls only or both.

grPhysPortHoldOff.name: grPhysPortHoldOff
grPhysPortHoldOff.description: This object specifies the time required for the port to remain idle before the next call can be issued.

grPhysPortPool.name: grPhysPortPool
grPhysPortPool.description: This object defines the resource pool that this physical interface belongs to.

grPhysWanStatsTable.name: grPhysWanStatsTable
grPhysWanStatsTable.description: A table containing information about physical WAN statistics.

grPhysWanStatsEntry.name: grPhysWanStatsEntry
grPhysWanStatsEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains information about a specific physical WAN interface. This table represents additional information not provided in the MIB II Interface table for WAN type interfaces.

grPhysWanStRxCrcErrs.name: grPhysWanStRxCrcErrs
grPhysWanStRxCrcErrs.description: The total number of frames that contained CRC errors.

grPhysWanStRxOverRunErrs.name: grPhysWanStRxOverRunErrs
grPhysWanStRxOverRunErrs.description: The total number of times that this interface has encountered an overrun condition.

grPhysWanStTxUnderRunErrs.name: grPhysWanStTxUnderRunErrs
grPhysWanStTxUnderRunErrs.description: The total number of times that this interface has encountered an underrun condition.

grPhysWanStRxAborts.name: grPhysWanStRxAborts
grPhysWanStRxAborts.description: The total number of received frames that were aborted.

grPhysWanStTxAborts.name: grPhysWanStTxAborts
grPhysWanStTxAborts.description: The total number of transmitted frames that were aborted.

grPhysWanStRxOctetErrors.name: grPhysWanStRxOctetErrors
grPhysWanStRxOctetErrors.description: The total number of octets that were received that were in error.

grPhysWanStTxOctetErrors.name: grPhysWanStTxOctetErrors
grPhysWanStTxOctetErrors.description: The total number of octets that were transmitted that were in error.

grPhysWanStLogicalIfIndex.name: grPhysWanStLogicalIfIndex
grPhysWanStLogicalIfIndex.description: This object indicates the logical port indexes (ifIndex) of all current calls if any exist. Each octet in the string represents one ifIndex. If the WAN port is idle (disconnected) then this object will return a zero length string.

grPhysWanStInCalls.name: grPhysWanStInCalls
grPhysWanStInCalls.description: The total number of inbound call received by this interface including those that failed.

grPhysWanStInFails.name: grPhysWanStInFails
grPhysWanStInFails.description: The total number of inbound calls that failed by this interface excluding those that failed for security reasons.

grPhysWanStInSecurityFails.name: grPhysWanStInSecurityFails
grPhysWanStInSecurityFails.description: The total number of inbound calls that failed because of authentication failures by this interface.

grPhysWanStOutCalls.name: grPhysWanStOutCalls
grPhysWanStOutCalls.description: The total number of outbound calls attempted by this interface including those that failed.

grPhysWanStOutFails.name: grPhysWanStOutFails
grPhysWanStOutFails.description: The total number of failed outbound call attempts by this interface excluding those that failed for security reasons.

grPhysWanStOutSecurityFails.name: grPhysWanStOutSecurityFails
grPhysWanStOutSecurityFails.description: The total number of outbound calls that failed due to authentication failures by this interface.

grLogicalTable.name: grLogicalTable
grLogicalTable.description: A table containing information about logical LAN destinations.

grLogicalEntry.name: grLogicalEntry
grLogicalEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains information about a specific logical interface to a local area network. Each logical LAN can support routing or bridging functions, these are considered virtual interfaces. The logical LAN can be permanently attached to a physical port (LAN or WAN) or it can float among available physical resources (WAN's only).

grLogicalDestName.name: grLogicalDestName
grLogicalDestName.description: The Ascii string associated with this logical destination LAN.

grLogicalTimeEnabled.name: grLogicalTimeEnabled
grLogicalTimeEnabled.description: This object indicates whether or not this interface is active only during certain periods as indicated by grLogicalTimeWindow.

grLogicalTimeWindow.name: grLogicalTimeWindow
grLogicalTimeWindow.description: This object indicates the actual window that this entry is to be active. Each day is represented by three octets, starting with Monday. The most significant bit of the first byte represents the 1st hour. The least significant bit of the third octet represents the 24th hour in the day. The next three octets represents the 24 hours of Tuesday etc thru Sunday. This object has no meaning if grLogicalTimeEnabled is disabled.

grLogicalType.name: grLogicalType
grLogicalType.description: This object determines whether this network interface is locally connected to a LAN or is connected to a LAN via a WAN. If this object is set to local(1) then this interface is associated with one of the physical LAN interfaces via the ifIndex. If this object indicates remote(2) then this network is reachable through a wide area network (WAN) as described in grLogWanTable.

grLogicalStatus.name: grLogicalStatus
grLogicalStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grLogicalStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grLogWanTable.name: grLogWanTable
grLogWanTable.description: A table containing configuration parameters for wide area network connections to logical LAN destinations that are accessible via serial interfaces. Each entry is logically tied to a logical LAN destination entry via ifIndex.

grLogWanEntry.name: grLogWanEntry
grLogWanEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains information about a specific logical interface to a remotely connected local area network. The instance of ifIndex used to index into this table is the same instance value used to index into the grLogicalTable.

grLogWanCmprsn.name: grLogWanCmprsn
grLogWanCmprsn.description: This object indicates whether or not this interface is to perform data compression.

grLogWanThshldOvrflw.name: grLogWanThshldOvrflw
grLogWanThshldOvrflw.description: This object determines if this interface is to attempt to bring up another link to the same destination if the traffic over the primary link exceeds a pre-determined threshold.

grLogWanThshld.name: grLogWanThshld
grLogWanThshld.description: This object determines the transmit threshold which when exceeded will cause an attempt to bring up another path. The returned value of this object has no meaning when threshold overflow is not enabled.

grLogWanConnTimer.name: grLogWanConnTimer
grLogWanConnTimer.description: When threshold overflow is enabled this object determines the amount of time in seconds that the average threshold must be exceeded before another link is established.

grLogWanDiscTimer.name: grLogWanDiscTimer
grLogWanDiscTimer.description: When threshold overflow is enabled this object determines the amount of time in seconds that the average threshold must be below before one of the multi-links is disconnected.

grLogWanSpoofing.name: grLogWanSpoofing
grLogWanSpoofing.description: This object indicates whether or not spoofing will occur on this link for routing information. If this object is disabled then periodic routing updates will be issued.

grLogWanStatus.name: grLogWanStatus
grLogWanStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grLogWanStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grLogWanPortTable.name: grLogWanPortTable
grLogWanPortTable.description: This configuration table identifies the characteristics of each potential transportation pipe to a remote site. Each entry in this table is associated with an entry in the grLogWanTable via its ifIndex. Multiple entries can be associated with a single entry in the grLogWanTable.

grLogWanPortEntry.name: grLogWanPortEntry
grLogWanPortEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains information about a single WAN resource used by a logical interface to a remote local area network. The instance of ifIndex used to index into this table is the same instance value used to index into the grLogicalTable. Multiple entries in this table having the same ifIndex usually indicates backup or multi-linking functionality.

grLogWanPortIndex.name: grLogWanPortIndex
grLogWanPortIndex.description: Identifies the port index associated with this entry.

grLogWanPortWanType.name: grLogWanPortWanType
grLogWanPortWanType.description: Indicates whether or not this link is to be used as a primary or secondary (backup) link.

grLogWanPortPhysIfIndex.name: grLogWanPortPhysIfIndex
grLogWanPortPhysIfIndex.description: Identifies the physical port ifIndex that is in use by this entry when the operational status is one of connecting(1), connected(2) or disconnecting(3). Otherwise this object will contain a zero value.

grLogWanPortPool.name: grLogWanPortPool
grLogWanPortPool.description: The name of the resource pool that will be used when attempting to allocate resources.

grLogWanPortRetry.name: grLogWanPortRetry
grLogWanPortRetry.description: Determines the retry count for dial up WAN circuits.

grLogWanPortRetryPeriod.name: grLogWanPortRetryPeriod
grLogWanPortRetryPeriod.description: Determines the retry period in seconds for dial up WAN circuits.

grLogWanPortPrepend.name: grLogWanPortPrepend
grLogWanPortPrepend.description: Indicates in most cases an Ascii string that will be prepended to the destination address.

grLogWanPortDestAddr.name: grLogWanPortDestAddr
grLogWanPortDestAddr.description: Indicates the destination address that this interface will call (ie: phone number).

grLogWanPortAdminStatus.name: grLogWanPortAdminStatus
grLogWanPortAdminStatus.description: The current desired state of this sub-layer.

grLogWanPortOperStatus.name: grLogWanPortOperStatus
grLogWanPortOperStatus.description: The current active state of this sub-layer.

grLogWanPortStatus.name: grLogWanPortStatus
grLogWanPortStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grLogWanPortStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grLogWanStatsTable.name: grLogWanStatsTable
grLogWanStatsTable.description: This table contains stats information for wide area connections to remote LAN's.

grLogWanStatsEntry.name: grLogWanStatsEntry
grLogWanStatsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains specific information about a single logical interface.

grLogWanStInUse.name: grLogWanStInUse
grLogWanStInUse.description: This object indicates the physical WAN port(s) currently in use by this logical destination. The WAN port ifIndex(es) are represented in a string of octets of varying length (depending on the number of active connections) where each octet contains the ifIndex ifIndex of the physical port.

grLogWanStUncmpsdRxOctets.name: grLogWanStUncmpsdRxOctets
grLogWanStUncmpsdRxOctets.description: The number of received octets after being decompressed.

grLogWanStCmpsdRxOctets.name: grLogWanStCmpsdRxOctets
grLogWanStCmpsdRxOctets.description: The number of received compressed octets.

grLogWanStUncmpsdTxOctets.name: grLogWanStUncmpsdTxOctets
grLogWanStUncmpsdTxOctets.description: The number of octets to be transmitted prior to being compressed.

grLogWanStCmpsdTxOctets.name: grLogWanStCmpsdTxOctets
grLogWanStCmpsdTxOctets.description: The number of transmitted compressed octets.

grLogWanStConnects.name: grLogWanStConnects
grLogWanStConnects.description: The total number of times this interface has attempted to establish a remote connection.

grLogWanStConnectFails.name: grLogWanStConnectFails
grLogWanStConnectFails.description: The total number of times this interface has attempted to establish a remote connection but failed.

grVirtualStatsTable.name: grVirtualStatsTable
grVirtualStatsTable.description: This table contains information with regards to virtual network interfaces.

grVirtualStatsEntry.name: grVirtualStatsEntry
grVirtualStatsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains specific information about a single virtual network interface whether it be a IP or IPX port.

grVSProtocolType.name: grVSProtocolType
grVSProtocolType.description: This object indicates what type of virtual port this information pertains to. Virtual bridge port stats can be obtained from RFC 1493 dot1dTpPortTable as well as grBridgePortStatsTable.

grVSNetAddr.name: grVSNetAddr
grVSNetAddr.description: The network address associated with this virtual interface (either a IP or IPX network address).

grVSIfIndex.name: grVSIfIndex
grVSIfIndex.description: The network interface associated with this virtual interface.

grVSRxPkts.name: grVSRxPkts
grVSRxPkts.description: The total number of packets that this virtual interface has received.

grVSTxPkts.name: grVSTxPkts
grVSTxPkts.description: The total number of packets that this virtual interface has transmitted.

grVSRxOctets.name: grVSRxOctets
grVSRxOctets.description: The total number of octets that this virtual interface has received.

grVSTxOctets.name: grVSTxOctets
grVSTxOctets.description: The total number of octets that this virtual interface has transmitted.

grVSTTLDiscards.name: grVSTTLDiscards
grVSTTLDiscards.description: The total number of packets that this virtual interface has discarded because their time to live within the router has exceeded. The time spent within the router is protocol specific.

grVSRxFilteredPkts.name: grVSRxFilteredPkts
grVSRxFilteredPkts.description: The total number of received packets that this virtual interface has filtered (as determined by the receive and destination Access Rights).

grVSTxFilteredPkts.name: grVSTxFilteredPkts
grVSTxFilteredPkts.description: The total number of packets that were filtered during the transmission process on this virtual interface (as determined by the receive and destination Access Rights).

grBridgingState.name: grBridgingState
grBridgingState.description: This object indicates the unit wide status for 802.1d bridging. Disabling this object overrides all interfaces that have bridging enabled.

grBrMaxTransitDelay.name: grBrMaxTransitDelay
grBrMaxTransitDelay.description: Determines the maximum time in 1/100 of a second that a bridged frame can be retained within the bridge before being discarded.

grBrFilterTestPackets.name: grBrFilterTestPackets
grBrFilterTestPackets.description: This object indicates the current state of the ethernet test packets filter option.

grProtFilterType.name: grProtFilterType
grProtFilterType.description: This object determines whether to forward or filter bridge packets that match an entry in the protocol filter table.

grProtFilterTable.name: grProtFilterTable
grProtFilterTable.description: A table containing protocol filtering information configured into the bridge.

grProtFilterEntry.name: grProtFilterEntry
grProtFilterEntry.description: Protocol filtering information configured into the bridge. Each entry contains a protocol Id which is used to filter/forward bridge packets based on the packets protocol type (ie: DECNET, IP etc).

grProtFilterId.name: grProtFilterId
grProtFilterId.description: This attribute identifies the protocol type to be filtered/forwarded.

grProtFilterStatus.name: grProtFilterStatus
grProtFilterStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grProtFilterStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grProtPriorityTable.name: grProtPriorityTable
grProtPriorityTable.description: A table containing protocol priority information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the priority in which frames will be transmitted on the wide area network links.

grProtPriorityEntry.name: grProtPriorityEntry
grProtPriorityEntry.description: Protocol priority information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management.

grProtPriorityId.name: grProtPriorityId
grProtPriorityId.description: This attribute identifies the protocol type to be prioritized.

grProtPriorityLevel.name: grProtPriorityLevel
grProtPriorityLevel.description: The priority assigned to the associated Portocol ID.

grProtPriorityStatus.name: grProtPriorityStatus
grProtPriorityStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grProtPriorityStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grBridgePortTable.name: grBridgePortTable
grBridgePortTable.description: This table defines additional bridging parameters (outside of those defined in RFC 1493) on bridging ports. The Bridge MIB (RFC 1493) is used to configure all other bridge port parameters.

grBridgePortEntry.name: grBridgePortEntry
grBridgePortEntry.description: Each entry in this table indicates the additional parameters in use by the bridge port.

grBrPortStpBpduFilter.name: grBrPortStpBpduFilter
grBrPortStpBpduFilter.description: This object determines if the Spanning Tree BPDU's are filtered or forwarded. If set to filter then this port will not send BPDU packets and any received BPDU's will be discared before reaching the Spanning Tree process.

grBrPortAllowedToGoDef.name: grBrPortAllowedToGoDef
grBrPortAllowedToGoDef.description: The default set of ports to which frames destined for this port have access. Each octet with the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying port 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. A bit value of '1' indicates access allowed.

grBridgePortStatsTable.name: grBridgePortStatsTable
grBridgePortStatsTable.description: This table contains bridge port statistics not available in the Bridge MIB.

grBridgePortStatsEntry.name: grBridgePortStatsEntry
grBridgePortStatsEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains bridge port stats.

grBrPortStRxOctets.name: grBrPortStRxOctets
grBrPortStRxOctets.description: This object indicates the number of received octets on this bridge port.

grBrPortStTxOctets.name: grBrPortStTxOctets
grBrPortStTxOctets.description: This object indicates the number of transmitted octets on this bridge port.

grBrPortStRxFilteredPkts.name: grBrPortStRxFilteredPkts
grBrPortStRxFilteredPkts.description: This object indicates the number of received bridge packets that were filtered because of access rights on the receive bridge port.

grBrPortStTxFilteredPkts.name: grBrPortStTxFilteredPkts
grBrPortStTxFilteredPkts.description: This object indicates the number of bridge packets that were filtered because of access rights on the output bridge port.

grSpanningTreeStatus.name: grSpanningTreeStatus
grSpanningTreeStatus.description: Indicates the unit wide status of 802.1d Spanning Tree.

grIpxRoutingEnable.name: grIpxRoutingEnable
grIpxRoutingEnable.description: Configures the router to enable IPX routing on a unit wide basis.

grIpxPrimaryNet.name: grIpxPrimaryNet
grIpxPrimaryNet.description: Configure the router with the primary network number for IPXWAN.

grIpxRipEnable.name: grIpxRipEnable
grIpxRipEnable.description: Configures the router to enable IPX RIP on a unit wide basis. Each logical port must still in turn have RIP enabled on a per port basis.

grIpxSapEnable.name: grIpxSapEnable
grIpxSapEnable.description: Configures the router to enable IPX SAP on a unit wide basis. Each logical port must still in turn have SAP enabled on a per port basis.

grIpxAccessRestrictEnable.name: grIpxAccessRestrictEnable
grIpxAccessRestrictEnable.description: This object indicates if this router is using the IPX Access Restriction table to filter out packets that are being routed.

grIpxAccessRestrictTable.name: grIpxAccessRestrictTable
grIpxAccessRestrictTable.description: The IPX Access Restriction configuration table.

grIpxAccessRestrictEntry.name: grIpxAccessRestrictEntry
grIpxAccessRestrictEntry.description: Contains information about a single IPX Access filter.

grIpxAccIndex.name: grIpxAccIndex
grIpxAccIndex.description: Identifies the unique entry in this table.

grIpxAccName.name: grIpxAccName
grIpxAccName.description: The name associated with this entry.

grIpxAccType.name: grIpxAccType
grIpxAccType.description: This object indicates if the router is to filter or forward IPX frames the match this access filter entry.

grIpxAccSrcNet.name: grIpxAccSrcNet
grIpxAccSrcNet.description: Defines the source IPX Network id to match on.

grIpxAccSrcNode.name: grIpxAccSrcNode
grIpxAccSrcNode.description: Defines the source IPX host id to apply when determining a match.

grIpxAccSrcSocketFrom.name: grIpxAccSrcSocketFrom
grIpxAccSrcSocketFrom.description: Defines the FROM range of source sockets to filter/ forward.

grIpxAccSrcSocketTo.name: grIpxAccSrcSocketTo
grIpxAccSrcSocketTo.description: Defines the TO range of source sockets to filter/ forward.

grIpxAccDstNet.name: grIpxAccDstNet
grIpxAccDstNet.description: Defines the destination IPX Network id to match on.

grIpxAccDstNode.name: grIpxAccDstNode
grIpxAccDstNode.description: Defines the destination IPX host id to apply when determining a match.

grIpxAccDstSocketFrom.name: grIpxAccDstSocketFrom
grIpxAccDstSocketFrom.description: Defines the FROM range of destination sockets to filter/forward.

grIpxAccDstSocketTo.name: grIpxAccDstSocketTo
grIpxAccDstSocketTo.description: Defines the TO range of destination sockets to filter/forward.

grIpxAccStatus.name: grIpxAccStatus
grIpxAccStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grIpxAccStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grIpxRouteTable.name: grIpxRouteTable
grIpxRouteTable.description: This table contains the static and learned IPX RIP information.

grIpxRouteEntry.name: grIpxRouteEntry
grIpxRouteEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains specific information about a single learned or static IPX RIP route.

grIpxRouteDest.name: grIpxRouteDest
grIpxRouteDest.description: This object indicates the destination network that this entries information pertains to.

grIpxRouteType.name: grIpxRouteType
grIpxRouteType.description: This object displays the type of route this entry is (ie: dynamically learned via RIP, static etc).

grIpxRouteHops.name: grIpxRouteHops
grIpxRouteHops.description: This object indicates the number of routers that must be passed through to reach the destination network associated with this entry.

grIpxRouteDelay.name: grIpxRouteDelay
grIpxRouteDelay.description: This object indicates the amount of time in ticks that a packet takes to reach the destination network associated with this entry. Each tick represents appx. 55 milliseconds.

grIpxRouteAge.name: grIpxRouteAge
grIpxRouteAge.description: This object indicates the age of this entry since the last RIP update in one hundreths of a second.

grIpxRouteNextHopNet.name: grIpxRouteNextHopNet
grIpxRouteNextHopNet.description: This object indicates the network portion of the next IPX router that IPX packets will be sent to in order to reach the destination network associated with this entry.

grIpxRouteNextHopNode.name: grIpxRouteNextHopNode
grIpxRouteNextHopNode.description: This object indicates the address portion of the next IPX router that IPX packets will be sent to in order to reach the destination network associated with this entry.

grIpxRouteIfIndex.name: grIpxRouteIfIndex
grIpxRouteIfIndex.description: This object indicates the logical port/interface (ifIndex) that this route was learned on.

grIpxRouteStatus.name: grIpxRouteStatus
grIpxRouteStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grIpxRouteStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grIpxServerTable.name: grIpxServerTable
grIpxServerTable.description: This table contains the learned and static IPX SAP information.

grIpxServerEntry.name: grIpxServerEntry
grIpxServerEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains specific information about a single learned or static IPX SAP server.

grIpxServerSapType.name: grIpxServerSapType
grIpxServerSapType.description: This object displays how this type of entry was learned (ie: dynamically learned via RIP, static etc).

grIpxServerAge.name: grIpxServerAge
grIpxServerAge.description: The age in one hundreths of a second since this router last heard from this server.

grIpxServerNet.name: grIpxServerNet
grIpxServerNet.description: This object contains the address of the network on which the server resides.

grIpxServerNode.name: grIpxServerNode
grIpxServerNode.description: This object contains the address of the node on which the server resides.

grIpxServerSocket.name: grIpxServerSocket
grIpxServerSocket.description: This object contains the socket number on which the server will receive service requests.

grIpxServerStatus.name: grIpxServerStatus
grIpxServerStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
grIpxServerStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

grIpxInReceives.name: grIpxInReceives
grIpxInReceives.description: This object reports the total number of IPX received packets including errored packets that this unit has processed.

grIpxInHdrErrors.name: grIpxInHdrErrors
grIpxInHdrErrors.description: The number of input datagrams discarded due to errors in their IPX headers, including bad checksums, transport control exceeded etc.

grIpxForwDatagrams.name: grIpxForwDatagrams
grIpxForwDatagrams.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IPX destination, as a result of which an attempt was made to find a route to forward them to that final destination.

grIpxInUnknownSockets.name: grIpxInUnknownSockets
grIpxInUnknownSockets.description: The number of locally-addressed datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported socket.

grIpxInDiscards.name: grIpxInDiscards
grIpxInDiscards.description: The number of input IPX datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded.

grIpxInDelivers.name: grIpxInDelivers
grIpxInDelivers.description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IPX user-protocols (including RIP and SAP).

grIpxOutRequests.name: grIpxOutRequests
grIpxOutRequests.description: The total number of IPX datagrams which local IPX user-protocols (including RIP and SAP) supplied to IPX in requests for transmission. This does not include any datagrams counted in grIpxForwDatagrams.

grIpxOutDiscards.name: grIpxOutDiscards
grIpxOutDiscards.description: The number of output IPX datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but which were discarded (ie: due to no resources).

grIpxOutNoRoutes.name: grIpxOutNoRoutes
grIpxOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IPX datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Note that this counter includes any packets counted in grIpxForwDatagrams which meet this `no-route' criterion.

grIpxLogicalTable.name: grIpxLogicalTable
grIpxLogicalTable.description: A table containing information about logical IPX LAN destinations.

grIpxLogicalEntry.name: grIpxLogicalEntry
grIpxLogicalEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains information about a specific IPX logical interface to a local area network. Each logical LAN can support routing or bridging functions, these are considered virtual interfaces.

grIpxLAccessDef.name: grIpxLAccessDef
grIpxLAccessDef.description: This object indicates what the default access right will apply to IPX packets that do not match any of the IPX Access Restrictions.

grIpxLRestrictions.name: grIpxLRestrictions

grCommunityName.description: The name of a Community that will be allowed access by the SNMP agent.

grCommunityTrapGeneration.description: This object indicates whether or not trap events are issued to the IP addresses listed for this community.

grPppLinkStatusTable.description: A table containing PPP-link specific variables for this PPP implementation. An extension table to pppLinkStatusTable in RFC 1471.

grPppLinkStatusEntry.description: Management information about a particular PPP Link.

grPppLinkStatusMultilink.name: grPppLinkStatusMultilink
grPppLinkStatusMultilink.description: Indicates whether PPP multi-link operation is in effect on this link. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

grPppLinkStatusLapB.name: grPppLinkStatusLapB
grPppLinkStatusLapB.description: Indicates whether lapb is being used at the link layer on this link. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

grPppIpxTable.name: grPppIpxTable
grPppIpxTable.description: A table containing IPXCP parameters for the local PPP entity.

grPppIpxEntry.name: grPppIpxEntry
grPppIpxEntry.description: IPXCP status information for a particular PPP link.

grPppIpxAdminStatus.name: grPppIpxAdminStatus
grPppIpxAdminStatus.description: The immediate desired status of the IPX network protocol. Setting this object to open will inject an administrative open event into the IPX network protocol's finite state machine. Setting this object to close will inject an administrative close event into the IPX network protocol's finite state machine.

grPppIpxOperStatus.name: grPppIpxOperStatus
grPppIpxOperStatus.description: The operational status of the IPX network protocol. If the value of this object is up then the finite state machine for the IPX network protocol has reached the Opened state.

grNewIpDefaultGateway.name: grNewIpDefaultGateway
grNewIpDefaultGateway.description: The grNewIpDefaultGateway trap indicates that the router has learned of a new default gateway (0.0.0.0). This will cause the router to start forwarding all IP traffic whose destination networks are not in the routing tables to this default gateway/router.

grIpStaticRouteOverride.name: grIpStaticRouteOverride
grIpStaticRouteOverride.description: The grIpStaticRouteOverride trap is generated by the router whenever a statically configured IP route has been overridden by a dynamically learned route (the dynamic route has better metrics).

grIpxStaticRouteOverride.name: grIpxStaticRouteOverride
grIpxStaticRouteOverride.description: The grIpStaticRouteOverride trap is generated by the router whenever a statically configured IPX route has been overridden by a dynamically learned route (the dynamic route has better metrics).

grPppLqmFailed.name: grPppLqmFailed
grPppLqmFailed.description: The grPppLqmFailed trap indicates that a PPP link is suffering from a loss of link quality. Normally this will cause retransmission and/or traffic errors which may prove the link to be unusable. The ifIndex will be provided in the variable bindings for this trap type.

grWanRetryThreshold.name: grWanRetryThreshold
grWanRetryThreshold.description: The grWanRetryThreshold trap is generated by the router whenever the maximum number of retries have been exhausted when attempting to contact a remote site on a specific serial interface. The ifIndex will provided in the variable bindings for this trap type.
